						<summary>

						<p>Two fragments of stone built in as door jambs, Sōmēśvarasvāmin temple, and on a stone pillar lying in the compound of the same temple.</p>						

						<p>This undated inscription may be assigned to the 10th century A.D., on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>Beginning lost. It gives the genealogy of the Eastern Chalukyas of Vēngi from Kubja-Vishnuvardhana. Other details are not known.</p>						

						</summary>
